arts.ttl: Leeds United’s Daniel Farke ranks as Championship’s best ever in new Sky Sports reveal
arts.sum: Leeds United squeezed past Swansea City with a dramatic 4-3 win in South Wales, and it puts them top of the pile after 16 games. It was a landmark occasion for Farke in the away dugout, hitting 200 games in the Championship from his time at Elland Road and Norwich City.

arts.ttl: 71 touches, 11 duels won: Another monster display from Leeds United bargain
arts.sum: James again at the heart as his square pass to Joel Piroe was cut out by Ben Cabango, turning into his own goal – before Solomon got his second, yet again with Leeds breaking beyond the sloppy high line, passing to the Israel international who converted. Leeds United came away from a dramatic encounter away at Swansea City with a huge 4-3 victory to move top of the table.

arts.ttl: Leeds go top of Championship as Gnonto settles seesaw Swansea thriller
arts.sum: Leeds went top of the Championship as Daniel Farke’s side twice came from behind to win a wild game at Swansea 4-3. Manor Solomon scored twice – his first Leeds goals – and Ben Cabango turned the ball into his own net before substitute Wilfried Gnonto struck a stoppage-time winner. Swansea had led through Harry Darling’s early opener and Liam Cullen – who scored for Wales against Iceland on Tuesday – restored their advantage on the stroke of half-time. Substitute Florian Bianchini appeared to have rescued a point for the hosts in the final minute, but Leeds went straight up the other end and Gnonto slid home from Daniel James’s pass to end their away-day blues. arts.sum: We are really happy with the three points because it was a difficult game today, I'm also pleased with my goals and it feels like a beginning for me.
